<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-804] build.xml: result of &quot;dist-src&quot; should support &quot;build-contrib&quot;</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-804</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently the packed src distribution would fail to run &quot;ant build-contrib&quot;.&lt;br/&gt;
It would be much nicer if that work.&lt;br/&gt;
In fact, would be nicer if you could even &quot;re-pack&quot; with it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For now I marked this for 2.1, although I am not yet sure if this is a stopper.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
            <key id="12362897">LUCENE-804</key>
            <summary>build.xml: result of &quot;dist-src&quot; should support &quot;build-contrib&quot;</summary>
                <type id="3" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/issuetypes/task.png">Task</type>
                                <priority id="4" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/priorities/minor.png">Minor</priority>
                    <status id="6" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/statuses/closed.png">Closed</status>
                    <resolution id="1">Fixed</resolution>
